thumb|left|Kurama and Naruto, with the other tailed beasts in a meeting.
In the anime, when Urashiki Ōtsutsuki began targeting Shukaku for its chakra, the tanuki agreed to be temporarily sealed in a small tea kettle and escorted to Konoha. While under Naruto's protection, Kurama, smug as ever towards Shukaku, laughed at how Himawari was treating the tanuki as a pet/toy. Kurama and Naruto later had a telepathic meeting with the other tailed beasts, though Matatabi, Kokuō, and Chōmei decided not to participate, and talked about their protection. Shukaku, vowing to get back at the fox for teasing it,...

wiki_sections.New Era: Part II:
[Boruto's Return Arc] {{main|Boruto's Return Arc}}
Three years after its temporary death, Kurama is revived as a much smaller, younger form. Its presence drew the attention of the Human God Trees, Jura and Hidari, who had mistaken Himawari for her father. As Team 10 retreated with Himawari from the God Trees, Kurama reached out to her within her mental realm, surprised that incarnations of the Ten-Tails were able to sense it. 
As Kurama introduced itself, it explained the situation to Himawari. Kurama surmised that its rebirth inside her came from her unique heritage, both being born of two strong bloodlines and inheriting some of its chakra already as the daughter of Kurama's previous jinchūriki. Himawari merely welcomed the fox, impressing Kurama at her maturity and acceptance of the situation. It also revealed to Himawari's compatibility to the fox's power is even greater than her father's was. As Himawari regained consciousness, Jura caught up to Himawari and forced them to the ground. When Inojin was impaled by Jura's Wood Release, the sight of her maimed friend enraged Himawari enough to access Kurama's power. Proud of how quickly Himawari adapted, it encouraged her to fight. Using her newfound abilities, Himawari healed herself and Inojin. She then proceeded to pummel Jura about, until the God Tree decided to take the fight more seriously and swiftly subdued her, prompting Kurama to admit that Himawari could not win. Instead, Boruto arrived to help his sister and teleported them away.
[Matsuri and Ryū Arc] {{main|Matsuri and Ryū Arc}}
thumb|Kurama training Himawari.
After the Human God Tree threat passed for the moment, Kurama began training Himawari within her mental realm. While sparing, it tried to make Himawari understand the importance of better chakra control to properly utilise her newfound powers. It explained to Himawari that her newfound status as a Jinchūriki is uniquely more akin to an actual tailed beast with the potency of her powers. Ultimately, deciding that Himawari needed time to process this news, it called the training for the day done.
{{-}}
[Naruto the Movie: Ninja Clash in the Land of Snow] {{main|Naruto the Movie: Ninja Clash in the Land of Snow}}
During the fight between Naruto and Dotō Kazahana, he managed to knock Naruto, who was at the disadvantage due to having the Chakra Negator on him, through the ice of the lake they were standing on, causing him to sink beneath the waters. However, as Naruto called upon the Nine-Tails for its chakra, which helped break the Chakra Negator, it allowed him to recover quickly and summon his shadow clones to overwhelm Dotō.
[Naruto the Movie: Guardians of the Crescent Moon Kingdom] {{main|Naruto the Movie: Guardians of the Crescent Moon Kingdom}}
During an attempt to escape the Land of the Moon, the three ninja hired by Shabadaba attacked, disabling Naruto, Kakashi, Sakura, and Lee with poison mists that slowed their reactions. The prince Michiru Tsuki was captured, but the emergence of the Nine-Tails' chakra allowed Naruto to repel the attacking ninja before the prince's son could be taken.
[Naruto Shippūden the Movie: Bonds] {{main|Naruto Shippūden the Movie: Bonds}}
When Naruto fought against the Zero-Tails to free Amaru from its influence, the malevolent spirit sensed the Nine-Tails within Naruto and expressed desire to obtain its power. The Zero-Tails then taunted Naruto and coaxed him into using the fox's power by saying that he couldn't save anyone without it. That made Naruto remember his failure in saving Sasuke and became emotionally unstable, which caused him to eventually enter his four-tailed form. After fighting with the spirit for a while, he turned back to normal when a seal on Naruto given by Jiraiya came off and reminded him of how the tailed beast chakra hurt his friends in which he immediately turned back to normal.
